But again, thank you very much for sharing
with us and taking your time, uh get, get um,

00:35:35.880 --> 00:35:44.460
I think we're gonna finish this one, uh.

00:35:46.740 --> 00:35:55.260
I think Lnn is making a question - 
we say, how much time it does it take,

00:35:56.400 --> 00:36:02.880
how much time does it take testing? [Susanna] That's another 
good question, um, well you can spend as much

00:36:02.880 --> 00:36:09.720
time as you like, of course, but you can test 
just one feature, and that will take from five

00:36:09.720 --> 00:36:16.800
to, I guess, mostly 10 minutes. We, of course, hope 
that you test all the the features, and you can

00:36:16.800 --> 00:36:20.820
also come back, because we have this iterative 
process, so then you can test it again and see

00:36:20.820 --> 00:36:25.620
the refinements. But, but you can just spend five or 
ten minutes and do one test, and we will be happy,

00:36:25.620 --> 00:36:30.180
and if you are really interested and keen then 
you can come back and test all the 10 features.

00:36:30.180 --> 00:36:36.060
And that will then take, maybe, one and a half 
hour or so, and you can also come back and do

00:36:36.060 --> 00:36:41.160
it more times, but but there's no, no specific 
requirements on time needed. So you can just

00:36:41.160 --> 00:36:45.660
do a short one and see if it's interesting and 
then, hopefully, you will stay on and do more tests.

00:36:50.460 --> 00:36:59.160
[Roberto] And then we have another question for Ahmed, uh 
